==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[disseminatus]], past participle of [[disseminare]], from prefix ''dis-'' "in all directions" + ''seminare'' "to plant or propagate", from ''semen, seminis'' "seed."

===Pronunciation===
IPA: dɪ'sɛm.ɪn.eɪt

===Transitive verb===
'''to disseminate'''
# To [[sow]] or [[broadcast]] as seed
# to [[scatter]] for [[growth]] and [[propagation]], like seed
# to [[spread]] [[abroad]]
# to [[diffuse]]; as, principles, ideas, opinions, and errors are disseminated when they are spread abroad for propagation.

===Intransitive verb===
'''to disseminate'''
# To become scattered.  ''The myth is disseminated throughout the southwest.''

